transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thanks for calling Viagra, this is Jimmy.

Speaker 2: How can I help you today?

Speaker 1: Yes, I called yesterday.

Speaker 2: I had ordered some, the AGB, I believe it's called,

Speaker 1: on the 19th and it was delivered like this past Friday,

Speaker 2: but it wasn't the right ones.

Speaker 1: I didn't get the lady's name that I spoke to, young lady,

Speaker 2: but I mentioned that she said she would take care of it.

Speaker 1: It would send me out the right thing

Speaker 2: and I was just wondering, I should have gotten her name,

Speaker 1: but also, didn't receive any emails yet,

Speaker 2: so I was kind of double checking the status

Speaker 1: if it's in the works or not.

Speaker 2: Do you want my email address?

Speaker 1: No, I was able to pull you up there, Mr. Goodman, right?

Speaker 2: Oh, okay, cool.

Speaker 1: Yes, that's correct.

Speaker 2: I do see that your order is in the pharmacy.

Speaker 1: It looks like that you're getting the Viagra AGB

Speaker 2: and hopefully it'll go out today, but I do see that.

Speaker 1: Oh, beautiful.

Speaker 2: They'll send that, they'll get an email

Speaker 1: like they did the first time, probably.

Speaker 2: It probably, once it gets shipped out,

Speaker 1: because by still being at the pharmacy,

Speaker 2: it hasn't shipped yet.

Speaker 1: Right.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Gotcha, okay.

Speaker 2: All right, sounds good.

Speaker 1: I appreciate it, Joe.

Speaker 2: All right, that's all I wanted to know.

Speaker 1: All right, have a good day.

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: You too.

Speaker 2: You too, bye-bye.
